reviewText: World Champion Sheamus vs. Dolph Ziggler - Holy WrestleMania Batman!!!...seriously we almost had an exact repeat of Mania with the World Title match going on first, Dolph getting a kiss, and almost it being the death of him in this match.  Sheamus grounded Dolph & even shoved him off the ropes to the floor at one point before Dolph regained the advantage & worked over Sheamus' neck with various super DDT's including a swinging version, Fameasser, and a face plant off the top rope.  Dolph continued to work over Sheamus with attempts at the sleeper with Sheamus being about to keep countering the hold into moves like the back breaker & White Noise.  This was a competitive match between both men who are heavily underrated in regards to not only their positions on the card but in the company.Tuxedo Match: Santino Marella vs. Ricardo Rodriquez - I could try to review this match but what's the point?  It was a bad attempt at comedy between these two characters to the point where the crowd was chanting "Boring."Intercontinental Champion Christian vs. Cody Rhodes - Cody tried to intimidate Christian by shoving him only for Christian to respond by slapping Cody off his feet & taking to offense right to him by knocking Cody off the apron in a unique way followed by a dropkick through the ropes before Cody eventually caught Christian & knocked him onto the apron.  Cody focused on Christian's arm after hanging it on the ropes followed by stomps, hammerlock, using the ring post, and even shoving Christian off the top rope with his shoulder hitting the apron on the way down but Christian fought back on the floor including using the steps for a tornado DDT.  Both men really stepped it up as they had counters & blocks to the others signature moves resulting in a match that definitely topped their previous PPV match.The Usos vs. Tyson Kidd & Justin Gabriel vs. Prime Time Players vs. Epico & Primo - This was to determine the #1 contenders to the Tag Team Titles after it was revealed earlier that A.W. didn't exercise Epico & Primo's rematch clause within the 30 day period causing them to lose their rematch.  This was your basically multi-man match as everyone had a moment to showcase themselves with the highlight being Tyson Kidd doing a frankensteiner that you had to see to believe but this match turned out to be all about A.W. showing how dedicated he was to "his team."Divas Champion Layla vs. Beth Phoenix - Another rematch from the previous PPV but this started out very differently as Beth started the match talking trash only for Layla trying to play her own mind games by mocking Beth by dancing with Beth's crown with the audience was completely silent for. Beth eventually caught Layla & kicked her out of the ring hitting the apron on the way down before being thrown into the barrier but Layla was able to keep staying one step ahead of Beth by countering her offense including the press slam into the DDT.  Unlike how the Cody/Christian rematch was a step up from the previous PPV, this was a step down as the beginning with Layla playing around mocking Beth just came off real bad & they didn't tell as good a story here as they previously did.Sin Cara vs. Hunico - A bonus match here from two people who've had their best matches in WWE against each other dating back to Hunico playing the role of the black Sin Cara.  This match however was easily their weakest encounter as Hunico was control a majority of the match grounding Cara causing him to play defense a majority of the match to the point where the crowd started chanting "We Want Ryder" as Cara only made a short comeback to win at the end.  It was nice to see Hunico do some aerial offense we haven't really seen from him since he was unmasked & stopped playing the black Sin Cara role months ago but this match just wasn't good & the botched finisher didn't help.WWE Champion C.M. Punk vs. Kane vs. Daniel Bryan - Throughout the night, we saw A.J. give good luck kisses to all of the competitors with Kane's being definitely the most affectionate.  With Kane definitely having the size & power advantage over Punk & Bryan, they worked together to try to take Kane out of the match with kicks including a double dropkick to the face to knock him down before Bryan did a suicide dive onto Kane on the outside with Punk following him coming off the top ropes onto both men.  Kane wouldn't go down easily as he was able to keep catching both men with hard hits like an uppercut to Bryan coming off the apron & a clothesline to Punk when he was running towards Bryan before working over Punk's ribs using the post & a body scissors.  There were various times where there were two men were either attacking or being attacked by the third man like Bryan taking both out when they were fighting over who gets to superplex Bryan while Punk & Kane later executing their own version of the Doomsday Device.  This was a good triple threat match as we know the "wrestling machines" that Punk & Bryan are with Kane not looking out of place for one moment during the match.Ryback vs. Dan Delaney & Rob Grymes - You got what you usually expect from a Ryback match but I have to say this was my favorite pre-match promo from the "victims" that I've heard yet.Steel Cage Match: John Cena vs. Big Show - As with the stipulations made on RAW & SmackDown, either John Cena or Johnny Ace was going to get fired at the end of this match as both Vince & Ace sat at ringside for this match.  In a nutshell, Big Show completely dominated John Cena in this match being the giant monster that we haven't seen from him in years as Cena's offense was hit & run out the cage whenever he had a chance only for Show to keep stopping him.  There was one point in the match where Show showcased his strength by yanking Cena to the top rope from the mat with one hand.  Vince & Ace did get involved on the outside before those who were victims of Big Show's attacks for the past month came out to get some revenge with one holding Show hostage by not allowing him to leave the cage before Cena was eventually able to leave the cage allowing Johnny Ace to get fired.  This was setup to be just like Cena's match with Brock Lesnar months earlier in that Cena got a lucky win that left the other guy still looking dominate & strong in defeat however this match wasn't good quality as they already haven't showed the chemistry they had against each other back in their U.S. Title feud almost a decade ago (their 2009 feud was AWFUL!) and the steel cage match really limits even more what they could do against each other just making this match just very dull & uneventful.This PPV was pretty much what you expected as the top championship matches (WWE/World) were good in quality & some solid undercard action (4 way tag & I.C. title), but unfortunately too many flops (Tuxedo Match, Divas, Cara/Hunico, Show/Cena) making this be one of those PPV's where there is just as much bad as there is good so unless you have some spare cash you won't miss, this is a PPV you can pass on as it's a step down from the roll the WWE was one with the Extreme Rules & even the Over The Limit PPV.

reviewText: WWENO WAY OUT 20121.[WORLD TITLE]SHEAMUS VS DOLPH ZIGGLER-this was a great opening match in my opinion with two underrated guys. The action here was fast paced and even made it look like a Wrestlemania repeat for Sheamus with Vickie Kissing Dolph and it almost being over. Dolph really looked great here controlling a large portion of the match delivering all kinds of moves. Sheamus of course is more of the power wrestler and retains his title after a great showing from both.2.[TUXEDO MATCH]SANTINO MARELLA VS RICARDO RODRIGUEZ-this match of course was the comedy match that really didn't deliver much. It did make me laugh a few times like the Alberto Roo's.3.[I-C TITLE]CHRISTIAN VS CODY RHODES-now back to the real action we are treated to another great match between two more guys who are underrated. In this match Cody is looking to get the title back he lost. Cody comes aggressive in this match working Christian over but Captain Charisma is no slouch. Good back and forth with both guys looking good here. Christian in the end hits the spear and retains his title.4.[FATAL FOUR WAY]TYSON KID & JUSTIN GABRIEL VS EPICO & PRIMO VS THE PRIME TIME PLAYERS VS THE USOS-I am a huge tag team wrestling fan and have always liked these multi team matches. Most of the time they are just fun matches added to the event for guys to hit their high spots. Then of course there are the classic multi team matches and fans who have been watching for years know what I am talking about. This one is the first one of course but sometimes a fun match is all you need. All the teams had their time to shine here with quick action and of course the high spots. The Prime Time Players end up winning the match and a shot at the tag titles.Here at this point Triple H comes out and challenges Brock Lesnar for a match at SummerSlam.5.[DIVAS TITLE]LAYLA VS BETH PHOENIX-I really didn't enjoy this match that much since Layla's comedic timing was off a little this time. The match was what most expect from a Diva's match sadly. Beth usually can save any match for me but with Layla winning in a quick match I just wasn't into it.6.HUNICO VS SIN CARA-I am a huge Sin Cara fan and have been watching him for years even before his WWE days wrestling as Mistico. Luckily living in Texas we get a lot of Spanish channels and the wrestling that comes with it. Any these two have always had good to great matches together but this one wasn't on par with their others. Hunico controls most of the match but Sin Cara makes the comeback for the win.7.[TRIPLE THREAT WWE TITLE]CM PUNK VS DANIEL BRYAN VS KANE-could be the best match of the night and that is not surprising since it has these three. Punk and Bryan are two of the best in WWE and Kane is the hard hitting vet. The action is excellent here as the two on one attacks are fun to watch. The comedic moments mixed in with the actual wrestling make this a great match that sees Punk keep the belt.8.RYBACK VS DAN DELANEY & ROB GRYMES-this of course is the usual Goldberg like match that they were giving Ryback. He comes out and makes quick work of these two smashing them.9.[STEEL CAGE MATCH]JOHN CENA VS BIG SHOW-the story here was that if Cena were to win Johnny would be fired as GM. Naturally Big Show was all about his power in this match taking to Cena. There is even a point where he yanks Cena up on the ropes. Cena on the other hand had to be a little quicker in this match. As far as cage matches go this was a good one with some good action. All the guys going out towards the end ensured that Cena won, so someone lost their job.There is an interview with CM Punk as a special feature on the DVD which is always good. Anyway this was a good event with some good matches. The storylines were continued and were well played out. I personally wanted Show to win so Johnny could stay but that is just me.

reviewText: This is a PPV you should get just for one thing. The end of People Power! The show had some great matches, but we all new it was all about the main event! The Steel Cage between John Cena VS The Big Show: if Cena loses, he is fired. But if The Big Show loses, John Laurinaitis is fired! We all came and just watched to see this results. This was a totally classic event because after this match, it became like Project X.
Title: N/A

reviewText: The World's title match between Sheamus & Dolph Ziggler was a hard-hitting back-and-forth bout and the same goes for the IC title match between Christian & Cody Rhodes. The Tuxedo match between Santino Marella & Ricardo Rodriguez was a dumb,cartoony comedy filler. The four way tag team match had alot of high-flying action and double team moves from all 4 way teams with a twist ending to boot. The Divas title match between Layla & Beth Phoenix started silly at first but then it better in the end. The Sin Cara-Hunico match had nice high-flying action with pretty good ground-and-pound action to boot. The 3 way bout for the WWE title(CM Punk-Daniel Bryan-Kane) was a hard-hitting,smash-mouth,double-teaming,nail-biting,heart-pounding match. The Handicap match between Ryback against the team of Dan Delaney & Rob Grymes was entirely pointless and it was just put on the card just to make The Goldberg Wannabe look good. The Steel Cage Match between John Cena & Big Show was a slow brawl but still a good brawl to say the least but only downside was the many run-ins from the many wrestlers who were attacked by Big Show in the past which made the bout look like a TNA match but not fully. Im not saying it was a bad match,Im just saying it could have done better without the run-ins. I give this PPV a 8 out of 10.

reviewText: WWE Presents NO WAY OUT 2012.WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP: SHEAMUS(c) vs. DOLPH ZIGGLER (w/ Vickie Guerrero)- Fun opening match to start us off. Del Rio got injured so they needed a new #1 contender for Sheamus. Ziggler won a 4-Way Elimination Match to get his shot. These guys tore the roof down. I thought this match was great. Sheamus gets the win and retains the World Heavyweight Championship. 4/5.TUXEDO MATCH: SANTINO MARELLA vs. RICARDO RODRIGUEZ- Comedy match, all it really is. 2/5INTERCONTIENTAL CHAMPIONSHIP: CHRISTIAN(c) vs. CODY RHODES- A fun midcard match here, two underrated guys putting on a really good match. Christian wins and retains the Intercontiental Championship. 3.5/5FOUR-WAY TAG TEAM MATCH FOR THE #1 CONTENDERHSHIP FOR THE TAG TITLES:PRIME TIME PLAYERS vs. USOS vs. EPICO & PRIMO vs. TYSON KIDD & JUSTIN GABRIEL- I found this match up to be very entertaining. Bunch of young studs doing what they do best. PTP get the win, with some help from.. ABE WASHINGTON! 3/5.DIVAS CHAMPIONSHIP: LAYLA(c) vs. BETH PHONIEX- Typical divas match here. Layla retains the title. 2.3/5TRIPLE THREAT MATCH FOR THE WWE CHAMPIONSHIP: CM PUNK(c) vs. DANIEL BRYAN vs. KANE- A very entertaining match up here. I wanted this to be the main event, but it wasn't. Still was the 'Main Event'. In my eyes, it was the 'Match of the Night'. You had two guys, who arguably the two 'Best' in the WWE. And you had a Big Red Monster into the mix. You get a heck of a match. CM Punk gets the win with a GTS, and retains the WWE Championship. 4.3/5.STEEL CAGE MATCH, EITHER CENA OR LAURINITUS GETS FIRED: JOHN CENA (w/ McMahon) vs. BIG SHOW (w/ Laurinitus)- This was a lot better than I thought it would be. With some stipulations, that kind of spoiled the match up, it  still was an entertaining match. John Cena gets the win and you know what that means... Big Johnny was FIRED! 3.7/5.WWE NO WAY OUT 2012. 7.5/10.

reviewText: I saw everything from start to finish and it was hot. I saw when John Cena was lifting John Laurainitis by his both shoulders and Vince McMahon came to him and he said that "John Laurainitis, you're fired" and then Cena gave Laurainitis the attitude adjustment after he fought the Big Show inside of a 15th foot high steel cage. That match was awesome and the match for the WWE Championship was also great. It was Kane VS. Daniel Bryan VS. C.M. Punk and it was great and A.J. was awesome when she gave a smile to Punk after the match finished when she was in the arms of Kane also the match for the World Heavyweight Championship between Sheamus VS. Dolph Ziggler was awesome. Sheamus gave a brogue kick to Ziggler to end the match. Thank you very much for sending me this DVD and I am going to say to you one more time it was great, sincerely yours, Zaida M Quijano.
